fulltitle: Geoffrey Keezer - Funky Stacks of Hipness: Double Diminished Chords (Preview)
description: Available at: https://openstudionetwork.com/keezer - Ever wonder what those thick, funky, hip chord structures are that composers like Duke Ellington and Thad Jones use? Quite often, they're some variation on a "double diminished" chord, which includes all the available notes in a diminished scale. In this extra-length single video, Geoffrey shows you how it's done! Includes the secret of the "Ellington sax voicing" and even the "triple diminished chord" from Herbie Hancock's "Eye of the Hurricane". (Level: Intermediate)
